div.p:
You see I rightly supposed that Campbells Travels lay within Mr Barrows xxx line of
                       demarcation. Southey had expressed interest in writing on John Campbell (1766–1840;
                           DNB), Travels in South Africa, Undertaken at the Request of the Missionary Society (1815);
                       see Southey to John Murray, 27 May 1815, Letter 2606. It was reviewed by John Barrow (1764–1848; DNB) in
                           Quarterly Review, 13 (July 1815), 309–340.
